caption: It was great. Had the fire shrimp and a glass of wine. Food was good. Waitress/ and waiter was also good.

To be honest, I am not sure why this place is so highly reviewed. From the moment we sat down I knew it was going to be a mistake. Our first sign should have been that it was the only restaurant downtown that was not completely booked up. The second sign should have been the decor and atmosphere... and the third sign should have been the water glasses with some yummy crunchy pieces on the outside of the cups. I ordered the ahi tuna steak... and I can tell you last night I woke up and almost threw up multiple times. I would also like to add: the seasonal veggie was brocolli (very exciting...) and I have had better seasoned food in a hospital. I cringe at the fact that we spent $60+ for 2 people (that was 1 drink and 1 entree per person) for a meal that was so lack luster and bland.  Normally I would not write this review and would just let it go... but the fact that I got sick from the food in the middle of the night was the deciding factor for me. 10/10 would NOT recommend.

The bonefish grill, located in BODO, is a large, low-ceiling'd restaurant lit with a warm yellow glow. The menu is filled with seafood, with a few options for land-loving diners. They offer a large selection of alcoholic beverages. Their food is quite good, with reasonably large, filling portions, and and a number of interesting flavour combinations. Their menu includes more standard options, such as salmon and cheese on a bed of greens, and ranging to a spicy tuna bowl with sweet mango and savory ahi. They are a good choice for large groups, and with reservations, can support groups of 20 or more. Their wait staff is pleasant, polite and jovial.

Great food but I have had very upsetting service issues.  I've eaten several times at bonefish grill for their excellent bang bang shrimp and I go back every time for that and their delicious lobster bisque.  The issue; my husband has a certified and trained service dog, she is quiet and does her job and most time waitresses don't even know we have her till way into the meal, that's how good she is. But every time we go into bonefish the hostesses tell us we have to go outside to eat with our dog. The last time we went, she was pushy about us needing to eat outside even though we told her that the dog is a service dog and we wanted to eat inside because it was getting dark and it was getting very cold outside and they didn't have the heaters on; she finally listened after the group behind us started making comments about her behavior and so they put us in the back and out of sight; but to our benefit, it was quiet.  Other than the rude hostess, the waitress was great, filling our drinks without bothering us and checking up on us all the time, she was fabulous and the food was on par.  I highly recommend this place for a great fine dining experience and for tasty seafood.  Maybe just skip the hostess or don't be disabled lol

I can't say enough about this place. The food was fabulous and the service was top notch.  We had a play to attend and needed to eat and leave quickly and the waitress was so accommodating and helpful. The prices are pretty typical for a seafood restaurant, so I didn't find them to be too high. We started with the bang bang shrimp (wow) and I had the trout with lemon cream sauce that was out of this world, and my husband had the teriyaki sea bass that was excellent as well. We will definitely be going back. Great portions, great service and love the atmosphere.

Wine is poured liberally which helps with the overall impression. Solid dinner with great service.

BoneFish has a lot of great options for anyone trying to eat a low carb diet. Stick to the fish options and veggies or try my favorite Lilly's Chicken. The food it always amazing but service can be slow from time to time. It all just depends on the day.

Worst service I’ve experienced in Downtown Boise. As we walked in the place had one group of four people sitting at the bar and a handful of other couples, the hostess was extremely rude and said it would be a 20-25 min wait.. ok I thought, maybe it’s short staffed.. then a waitress walked up and went off to the host about how her customers were being douche bags and he needed to deal with them. We decided to try the bar and after not receiving service for an unexplained amount of time we decided to close our tabs and move on.. I don’t review much, but when you have an experience as bad as this, with people who genuinely don’t care about your experience, it’s justified to let everyone know! Boise has better options!

I should give two separate reviews. 1. The pork chop with garlic whipped potatoes and spinach  was excellent. 2. The fish tacos really missed on the quantity of fish in the tacos bur the management brought more to add to the meal. Other then being a bit pricey, everything was good (not great).

Our food and drink for the evening was very good despite the food being much slower than expected coming from the kitchen but Judah the manager made everything right and we will certainly return because of his high level of service.

As a business traveler it's often hard to find decent restaurants to eat at that aren't always garbage. Good food at reasonable prices in a casual, but upscale setting.  I recently traveled to Boise for work and visited Bonefish Grill with my coworkers. We enjoyed this restaurant.  The service during our visit was good, not too many visits to the table by our server to be disruptive or too few to be irritating. Need that water glass filled more than once? Got it covered.  The wine by the glass is reasonably priced and the menu offers a good number of choices. Likewise, the dinner menu itself offers a good array of choices; I chose the Chilean Sea Bass with Jasmine rice for my entree. The fish was perfectly cooked and the rice was neither dry or too sticky; great flavor for both. If you don’t like food that used to swim, they have a nice filet mignon for you.  Based on my experience visiting this restaurant, I would definitely go back.
The food was great, the service was good, the ambiance was romantic.

Food amazing! The Bang Bang shrimp is a must try! The only complaint I had was that my stomach wasn't big enough for more. Even the drinks were authentic and made with perfection. Not offensively strong or too weak. Very high standards at this establishment. I left with a little buzz and forgot to shake the chef's hand. Next time I will for sure.

The wait wasn't bad at all with the fun music and atmosphere! And the fish tacos were the best I've had in awhile, which is surprising in a state so far from the ocean! It's a little pricy but worth it for the portions and FREE BREAD is always a plus!

Great drinks, food, and atmosphere! They were very accommodating of our large group, with people showing up at all different times. Next time I go, however, I'll be ordering the petite filet, which looked amazing (I had a serious case of meal envy when my neighbor's dinner arrived!).
